claims:
1. An object-collection system, comprising:
a ground-based object picker assembly configured to capture a target object;
a camera configured to capture a plurality of images in a direction of movement of the ground-based object picker assembly;
a memory that stores computer instructions;
a processor configured to execute the computer instructions to:
capture, via the camera, a plurality of images as the ground-based object picker assembly moves along the ground;
identify a target object in the plurality of images based on an analysis of features of the target object;
track relative movement of the target object, with respect to the ground-based object picker assembly, through the plurality of images;
determine a position of the ground-based object picker assembly relative to the target object based on an analysis of the plurality of images;
align the ground-based object picker assembly with the target object based on the tracked relative movement of the target object, with respect to the ground-based object picker assembly, and the determined position of the ground-based object picker assembly;
determine when the target object is at a position in at least one of the plurality of images to trigger pick up the target object; and
in response to determining that the target object is at the position to trigger pick up the target object, instruct the ground-based object picker assembly to pick up the target object.
2. The object-collection system of claim 1, wherein the processor is configured to determine the position of the ground-based object picker assembly by further executing the computer instructions to:
employ an artificial neural network to identify a position of the ground-based object picker assembly within the plurality of images.
3. The object-collection system of claim 1, wherein the processor is configured to align the ground-based object picker assembly with the target object by further executing the computer instructions to:
move the ground-based object picker assembly horizontally to align with the target object.
4. The object-collection system of claim 1, wherein the processor is configured to align the ground-based object picker assembly with the target object by further executing the computer instructions to:
instruct the ground-based object picker assembly to autonomously move to align the ground-based object picker assembly with the target object.
5. The object-collection system of claim 1, wherein the processor is configured to further execute the computer instructions to:
instruct the ground-based object picker assembly to pick up the target object in response to alignment of the ground-based object picker assembly with the target object when the target object is within range of the ground-based object picker assembly.
6. The object-collection system of claim 1, wherein the processor is configured to further execute the computer instructions to:
instruct the ground-based object picker assembly to move to a pick-up height to pick up the target object in response to the target object being within range of the ground-based object picker assembly and the ground-based object picker assembly being aligned with the target object; and
instruct the ground-based object picker assembly to move to a storage height after the target object is picked up, wherein the ground-based object picker assembly is within view of the camera when in the storage height.
